Scope note: the four slash commands shipped by Section D (/undo,
/changelog, /hooks, skill:*) are interactive TUI flows that require
pi-tui + a real terminal. On macOS without coreutils `timeout`,
`script(1)` + time-boxed runs are fragile and rarely reproducible
from session to session (the `expect` helper would need to grow
into the test harness itself). The practical substitute is unit
coverage against the same code paths the TUI would exercise, which
is what Section D ships.


D.6.1 — /undo rolls back via session.rollback(n_turns_back)
----------------------------------------------------------------
Unit coverage: apps/kimi-cli/test/slash/undo.test.ts (3 cases)
  - happy: calls wireClient.rollback(sessionId, 1) and returns a
    reload action with action='undo'
  - wire error: "rollback failed: <core error message>"
    surfaced through the slash output
  - missing method: wireClient without `rollback` degrades
    gracefully with a clear status message

Core handler already pinned by Phase 18 §F tests:
  packages/kimi-core/test/router/wire-methods-phase18-f.test.ts
  verifies `session.rollback` zod schema uses `n_turns_back` (not
  `n_turns`) so the /undo payload shape is correct.

$ grep -n "not yet implemented" apps/kimi-cli/src/slash/shell-commands.ts
(no matches — the /undo stub was removed in this slice)


D.6.2 — skill:* dynamic dispatch with built-in precedence
----------------------------------------------------------------
Unit coverage: apps/kimi-cli/test/slash/skill-dispatch.test.ts (5 cases)
  - unknown slash name + listSkills returns a matching skill
    → activateSkill called with the remaining args
  - unknown slash name + listSkills returns empty
    → "Unknown command /name" surfaced
  - wireClient without listSkills
    → graceful "Unknown command" without crash
  - listSkills throws → annotated error in output
  - built-in /help vs a skill named help → built-in wins


D.6.3 — /changelog prints the latest section
----------------------------------------------------------------
Unit coverage: apps/kimi-cli/test/slash/changelog.test.ts (6 cases)
  - parseLatestChangelogSection (pure):
      • regular [Unreleased] + [x.y.z] structure → first section
      • file without any `##` headers → returns "empty"
      • single section all the way to EOF → returns that section
  - loadLatestChangelog (with deps):
      • happy path finds CHANGELOG.md up the tree
      • no CHANGELOG.md → "No CHANGELOG.md found" message
      • CHANGELOG.md with only the intro paragraph → "empty" message

The shipped CHANGELOG.md (repo root, ts/CHANGELOG.md) follows Keep
a Changelog + semver, exact format pinned by manual read in the
Slice D commit message body.


D.6.4 — /hooks prints initialize.capabilities.hooks.configured
----------------------------------------------------------------
Unit coverage: apps/kimi-cli/test/slash/hooks.test.ts (4 cases)
  - formats hook entry as "event → matcher → command"
  - empty configured list → "No hooks configured."
  - missing initialize response → graceful "Hooks information
    unavailable"
  - wireClient without getInitializeResponse getter → same
    graceful fallback

The CLI wire client's `getInitializeResponse()` lazy-builds the
response on first access from `deps.config.hooks` so /hooks works
without an explicit handshake round-trip.


